oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:title: It's Our Land - Inaugural Broadcast
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:description: The recording features the inaugural broadcast of the thirteen part series ""It's Our Land"" presented by WSM Radio. The tape features performances by: Eddy Arnold (musician), Snooky Lanson (musician), Bradley Kincaid (musician), Roy Acuff (musician), and the WSM Chorus (musical group). The tape is labeled Acuff's tape number seven of an unidentified number. The recordings are from a variety of unidentified dates.
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:creator: Eddy Arnold; Snooky Lanson; Bradley Kincaid; Roy Acuff; WSM Chorus
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dcterms:tableOfContents: (00:00) Eddy Arnold is introduced by Snooky Lanson and Bradley Kincaid for the inaugural broadcast of ""It's Our Land"" presented by WSM Radio -- (01:19) Traveling Broadens One (Eddy Arnold) -- (03:38) I've Got a Church (Roy Acuff) -- (08:43) Native Born and Foreign Born Has Made Our Country Great (Snooky Lanson) -- (10:38) These Bones Gwine Rise Again (Bradley Kincaid and the WSM Chorus) -- (14:37) The Ballad of Treason (Bradley Kincaid) -- (16:16) [Unidentified] (WSM Chorus) -- (20:12) Atom and Evil (Bradley Kincaid) -- (22:13) Freedom Train Track (Bradley Kincaid) -- (22:52) Wonderful World (Snooky Lanson and the WSM Chorus) -- (25:20) I'm Proud to be Me (Bradley Kincaid) -- (26:22) Commodore Gray (Snooky Lanson and the WSM Chorus) -- (28:46) Prayer of Rededication (Eddy Arnold, Roy Acuff, Bradley Kincaid and Snooky Lanson) -- (30:25) Freedom Train (Get on Board) (WSM Chorus)
